Program: The History Hour
Title: Medicine in World War One
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0w3
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 27 Aug 2017
In BBC archive recordings, veterans tell the story of how medical care dealt with the horrors of WW1. Plus when Germany put Nazis on trial, race riots in London's Notting Hill in 1958, and in East Germany in 1992. And the inventors of Botox. Photo: Australian wounded on the Menin Road on the Western Front, 1917 (Hulton Archive/Getty Images) Show less